Doc covers what the basics of MIst and its installation 

Mist is like a browser for blockchain. It is the easiest way to get the look and feel of the entire blockchain.

Starting with the explanation and information on how to start ethereum :
https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Ethereum-Development-Tutorial
https://blog.ethereum.org/2016/07/12/build-server-less-applications-mist/

  Installing MIST using:
  https://github.com/ethereum/mist
  
  Mist required NPM and meteor the following dependencies:
    - Electron
    - Node v6.0
    - Yarn package manager
   
This example of a blockchain application that can be run on the mist browser directly - STAKE VOICE
https://github.com/ethereum/mist/releases/tag/0.8.0
